#compdef xlsx
# ============================================================================
# xlsx - SheetJS spreadsheet data CLI
#         (TypeScript/Node, Apache-2.0)
#
# Author : SheetJS LLC + community
#           (founded by Reuben Ten-Pow +
#           Vamsi Anjur; commercial
#           steward of the SheetJS
#           ecosystem)
# Upstream: https://github.com/SheetJS/sheetjs
#           (new home: https://git.sheetjs
#           .com/SheetJS/sheetjs)
# npm pkg : xlsx
#
# `xlsx` is the canonical Node spreadsheet
# CLI shipped by the SheetJS LLC project,
# providing command-line access to the
# SheetJS Spreadsheet Data Toolkit's
# parsing + serialization capabilities.
# Handles the broadest range of spreadsheet
# formats of any open-source library across
# any language ecosystem.
#
# Supported formats (read + write):
#   - **XLSX** (Office Open XML; modern
#     Excel format since 2007)
#   - **XLSM** (macro-enabled XLSX)
#   - **XLSB** (Excel Binary format)
#   - **XLS** (legacy Excel 97-2003)
#   - **XLML** (Excel 2003 XML)
#   - **ODS** (OpenDocument Spreadsheet;
#     LibreOffice + OpenOffice)
#   - **FODS** (Flat OpenDocument)
#   - **CSV** (Comma-Separated Values)
#   - **TXT** (Tab-Separated Values)
#   - **DIF** (Data Interchange Format;
#     VisiCalc era)
#   - **SYLK** (Symbolic Link; multiplan
#     1980s format)
#   - **HTML** (HTML table extraction)
#   - **DBF** (dBASE database files)
#   - **RTF** (Rich Text Format tables)
#   - **PRN** (formatted text)
#   - **ETH** (EtherCalc native format)
#   - **NUMBERS** (Apple Numbers; read
#     only)
#
# Distinguishing features vs alternatives:
#   - **Broadest format support** (~17
#     spreadsheet formats - far more
#     than calamine + excelize + exceljs
#     combined)
#   - **Pure JavaScript** (no native
#     bindings; runs in Node + browsers
#     + Deno + Bun + Cloudflare Workers
#     + serverless functions)
#   - **Battle-tested** (~14 years of
#     development; used by Salesforce +
#     Microsoft + Google + AWS + many
#     Fortune 500 enterprises)
#   - **CSF (Common Spreadsheet Format)**
#     - the SheetJS internal
#     representation that all formats
#     normalize to + de-normalize from
#   - **Both reading + writing** for all
#     major formats (some other libraries
#     only handle one direction)
#   - **Commercial steward** (SheetJS LLC
#     provides paid support + LTS
#     releases for enterprise users)
#
# Use cases:
#   - Format conversion (XLS ↔ XLSX ↔
#     ODS ↔ CSV in shell pipelines)
#   - Quick spreadsheet inspection in
#     terminal
#   - Batch processing scripts (process
#     multiple spreadsheets without
#     opening Excel)
#   - Server-side spreadsheet generation
#     (Node.js services producing Excel
#     reports for download)
#   - Build-time data pipeline
#     (extract data from spreadsheets in
#     CI/CD workflows)
#
# Usage:
#   xlsx [options] [file]
#
# Common flags (commander.js):
#   -f, --file <file>              - use
#                                     specified
#                                     workbook
#                                     (input)
#   -s, --sheet <sheet>            - print
#                                     specified
#                                     sheet
#                                     (name
#                                     or
#                                     1-indexed
#                                     position;
#                                     default
#                                     first
#                                     sheet)
#   -L, --listSheets, --list-sheets - list
#                                     sheet
#                                     names
#                                     in
#                                     the
#                                     workbook
#   -t, --type <type>              - output
#                                     format
#                                     (csv +
#                                     txt +
#                                     html +
#                                     json +
#                                     formulae;
#                                     default
#                                     csv)
#   -b, --book <type>              - output
#                                     workbook
#                                     format
#                                     (xlsx +
#                                     xlsm +
#                                     xlsb +
#                                     xls +
#                                     xlml +
#                                     ods +
#                                     fods +
#                                     csv +
#                                     txt +
#                                     html +
#                                     dif +
#                                     sylk +
#                                     prn +
#                                     dbf +
#                                     eth)
#   -o, --output <file>            - write
#                                     output
#                                     to
#                                     specified
#                                     file
#                                     (default
#                                     stdout)
#       --read-only                - read-
#                                     only
#                                     mode
#                                     (skip
#                                     writing)
#       --all                      - read
#                                     all
#                                     sheets
#                                     (default
#                                     first
#                                     sheet
#                                     only)
#       --pretty                   - pretty-
#                                     print
#                                     JSON
#                                     output
#                                     (only
#                                     applies
#                                     when
#                                     --type
#                                     json)
#       --quiet                    - suppress
#                                     console
#                                     output
#                                     except
#                                     errors
#   -v, --version                  - output
#                                     the
#                                     version
#                                     number
#   -h, --help                     - output
#                                     usage
#                                     information
#
# Positional argument:
#   [file]                         - input
#                                     workbook
#                                     file
#                                     (alternative
#                                     to
#                                     --file)
#
# Example invocations:
#   # Convert XLSX to CSV (default
#   # behavior: first sheet)
#   xlsx workbook.xlsx > output.csv
#
#   # Or via file flag
#   xlsx -f workbook.xlsx > output.csv
#
#   # List sheets in workbook
#   xlsx -L workbook.xlsx
#
#   # Convert specific sheet
#   xlsx -s "Q4 Sales" -t csv workbook.xlsx
#
#   # Convert by 1-based sheet index
#   xlsx -s 2 -t csv workbook.xlsx
#
#   # Output to JSON
#   xlsx -t json workbook.xlsx > data.json
#
#   # Pretty-printed JSON
#   xlsx -t json --pretty workbook.xlsx > data.json
#
#   # Convert XLS to modern XLSX
#   xlsx -b xlsx -o new.xlsx legacy.xls
#
#   # Convert XLSX to ODS (LibreOffice
#   # format)
#   xlsx -b ods -o output.ods workbook.xlsx
#
#   # Convert CSV to XLSX
#   xlsx -b xlsx -o output.xlsx data.csv
#
#   # Read all sheets into JSON
#   xlsx --all -t json workbook.xlsx > all.json
#
#   # Convert XLS legacy to XLSB (binary)
#   xlsx -b xlsb -o compact.xlsb legacy.xls
#
#   # Show version
#   xlsx --version
#
